latestIgtvVideos.title: Inquilab: A Documentary
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Inquilab 
An is either revolution or plagiarism- Paul Gauguin
has had a cult of western culture and has seen him behaving like a religion. And the most influenced cities are Mumbai specially encompasses a fare set of people who made judgments and outlook very publicly, and art has been one of the favored mediums used for youth. And graffiti has been one of those western qualities that are to be portrayed precisely and publicly but the definition of graffiti does not end at vandalism in India, it is rather different ways in which the visual pleasures of the slums of beautification to a boring street or even a full time carrier option This documentary will bring an understanding of art through the eyes of a graffiti artist in Mumbai and will present the struggle, motivation, beliefs and future of Graffiti in Mumbai. With acceptance comes motivation and motivation brings about a uprising Let's enable art to be a weapon to revolution- to Inquilab a documentary
 project by students of Digital Academy The Film School, Andheri

Turning an idea into something you can touch. Watch how this 3D MDF graffiti piece came to life from lines on paper to sculpted attitude

#Nmegraffiti #Mumbaigraffiti #Graffitininida #WoodenGraffiti #3DArt #GraffitiSculpture #MDFArt #StreetArtStudio #GraffitiOnWood #UrbanArt #ArtistLife

I turned chaos into curves when I crafted this 3D wooden graffiti piece. I’ve always wanted to experiment with cutting shapes, and working with MDF was a game-changer. From sketch to sawdust, every layer tells a story.

This piece is 20” x 4”, and every curve has its own rhythm and rebellion. It’s a reminder that graffiti is more than just paint it’s about making a statement.

#Nmegraffiti #Mumbaigraffiti #Graffitininida #WoodenGraffiti #3DArt #GraffitiSculpture #MDFArt #StreetArtStudio #GraffitiOnWood #UrbanArt #ArtistLife #CreativityUnleashed”
